## GDL [/definitions/gdl]

Management of GDL resources in the system. 

### List all guides [GET /definitions/gdl]

List all available guides in the system

+ Response 200 (application/json) 

    `200 OK` is returned when the resources are succesfully retrieved. 

    + Body

            [{
                    "guideId": "GuideOne.v1",
                    "validTo": "2016-05-26T12:04:43",
                    "createdTimeStamp": "2016-05-26T12:02:01",
                    "concept": "Guide one"
                },
                {
                    "guideId": "GuideTwo.v1",
                    "createdTimeStamp": "2016-05-26T12:04:43",
                    "concept": "Guide two"
                }
            ]

### Upload guide [POST /definitions/gdl]

+ Request 
    
    + Body 

            {
              "gdl": "<the gdl as a UTF-8 string>"
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json) 

    `201 Created` is returned when the guide has been successfully uploaded to the server.

    + Headers

            Location: /definitions/gdl/{guideId}


+ Response 400 

    `400 Bad Request` is returned when the server was unable to upload the guide. 

    + Body 

### Get guide [GET /definitions/gdls/{guideId}]

+ Parameters
    
    + guideId (string) - the guideId 

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    `200 OK` is returned when the guide is succesfully retrieved. 

    + Body 

                "(GUIDE) <\n\tgdl_version = <..... "
